[VS2-339] Open Access Collection approval execution

Background:
TBC

User Story:
As a DPO Officer, I want data of an approved Open Access Collection to be provisioned so that User can access it.

Acceptance criteria:
GIVEN an Open Access Collection WHEN capturing TA Lead approvals THEN formal signatures with complete audit trail documentation and timestamps are recorded.
GIVEN a cross-TA data collection WHEN TA Lead approvals are required THEN all relevant TA Leads must provide signatures for their applicable study lists before provisioning can proceed.
GIVEN a cross-TA approval process WHEN any single TA Lead fails to provide signature approval THEN the data collection cannot be enabled for users in any therapeutic area involved.
GIVEN an approved Open Access Collection WHEN no outstanding legal or ethical checks are present THEN it is submitted for execution.
GIVEN an approved Open Access Collection WHEN required signed documentation is present (AoT, User training, version baseline) THEN it is submitted for execution.
GIVEN an approved Open Access Collection WHEN required other minimum info gates are met (definitive asset list, modalities/sources, environments, virtual team/Users) THEN it is submitted for execution.
GIVEN a metadata change WHEN detection of access invalidates its entry THEN policy auto-revokes and stakeholders are notified.
GIVEN an approved AoT WHEN all required TA Lead signatures are obtained THEN Collectoid automatically provisions authorised studies to specified users.
GIVEN cross-TA approval requirements WHEN all TA Lead signatures are collected THEN provisioning proceeds only after all approvals are received.